mrigger added on 2019-08-29 13:46:09:
Consider the test case below:
CREATE TABLE t0(c0);
CREATE INDEX i0 ON t0(1) WHERE c0 NOT NULL;
INSERT INTO t0(c0) VALUES (NULL);
SELECT * FROM t0 WHERE ~((('') BETWEEN (t0.c0) AND TRUE)); -- unexpected: row is not fetched
Unexpectedly, the row is not fetched. The expression should evaluate to TRUE:
SELECT ~('' BETWEEN t0.c0 AND TRUE) IS TRUE FROM t0; -- TRUE
